div.div: Commented on #4 Suggestion - Allow passing of variables or variable in event

What's the point, you're already defining the data. Assign it to a local or table inside your resource, instead of sending it to ox_target and having it sent back. The point of ox_target is to stop horrible design patterns that people constantly implement In fact, this should already be possible, despite being pointless in most situations (I believe it's solely there for the sake of backwards-compatibility). I think you misunderstood my idea. This data can be dynamic and change from the resource calling it to the resource aimed to receieve it. if we go to basics. test.lua function (type) if type == "type1" then (7 more lines were trimmed) rather than making 3 different events for this function we can make one that passes the type value. In the end it reduces duplicated code with minor tweaks.
